  <section class="content-section bg-light" id="faq">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Safe Engineer — FAQ</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Common questions about professional safe engineering services.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-with-card">
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <details class="faq-item" open>
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>What safe brands do you work with?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">All major manufacturers including Chubb, Phoenix, Dudley, Yale, Burton, SentrySafe, Honeywell, Securikey, De Raat, and many more. Call to confirm your specific make and model.</div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>How much does safe opening cost?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">Cost depends on the safe type, the locking mechanism, and the method required to open it. William provides a clear, written quote before any work begins — no hidden fees or surprises.</div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>How long does safe opening take?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">Non-destructive opening typically takes 30 minutes to a few hours depending on the safe make, age, and locking mechanism. A realistic time estimate is given at the time of quoting.</div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>Can you travel to my location anywhere in the UK?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Safe engineering is available UK-wide by appointment. Priority response is given to North London and Greater London, but William regularly travels nationally for this specialist work.</div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>What is the difference between a combination safe and a key safe?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">A combination safe opens via a dial or electronic keypad code. A key safe requires a physical key. Some safes use both. William handles opening, repair, and combination or key changes for all types.</div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">
              <span>Do you handle commercial and high-security safes?</span>
              <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">Yes. William has experience with commercial-grade safes, deposit safes, fire-rated data safes, floor and wall safes, and gun cabinets. All work is carried out discreetly and professionally.</div>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-sidebar">
          <div class="response-time-card">
            <div class="rtc-header">
              <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i>
              <h3>Appointment</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="rtc-time">By Appt.</div>
            <p class="rtc-note">UK-wide — contact for availability</p>
            <div class="rtc-divider"></div>
            <div class="rtc-stat">
              <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i>
